03/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Israel said Monday (August 2nd) that it will co-operate with an international panel that will probe an Israeli raid against a Turkish-led aid flotilla to Gaza that left nine people dead on May 31st. 
The four-member panel, urged by UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon, will be chaired by former New Zealand Prime Minister Geoffrey Palmer and will include representatives of both Israel and Turkey. 
It will begin work on August 10th and is expected to submit its first report by mid-September. 
(Haaretz, Hurriyet - 02/08/10)
